{"version":3,"kind":"Article","sha256":"e137deba27574d6ca70609a865e8a2efbfc4da0c3087df87dce50655593c7984","slug":"index","location":"/index.md","dependencies":[],"frontmatter":{"title":"Copperline","parts":{"abstract":{"mdast":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"block","data":{"part":"abstract"},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":1,"column":1},"end":{"line":7,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Copperline is a cycle-driven Commodore Amiga emulator (OCS, ECS, and\nAGA) written in Rust. This document covers using the emulator,\nconfiguring machines from the A500 to the A4000 and CD32, describing\nZorro expansion boards, the browser (WebAssembly) build, the\ninteractive and headless debuggers, and the\ninternal architecture: the per-colour-clock chip-bus timing model, the\nchipset modules, and the beam-event-replay video pipeline.","position":{"start":{"line":1,"column":1},"end":{"line":1,"column":1}},"key":"QnTANkOUtt"}],"key":"eqtYO5iOPa"}],"key":"P7gsxAyNXF"}],"key":"BRuPVAz0yF"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Copperline","content_includes_title":false,"authors":[{"nameParsed":{"literal":"Andrew Hutchings","given":"Andrew","family":"Hutchings"},"name":"Andrew Hutchings","id":"contributors-myst-generated-uid-0"}],"github":"https://github.com/LinuxJedi/Copperline","keywords":["amiga","emulator","ocs","ecs","rust"],"source_url":"https://github.com/LinuxJedi/Copperline/blob/main/docs/index.md#parts.abstract","edit_url":"https://github.com/LinuxJedi/Copperline/edit/main/docs/index.md#parts.abstract"}}},"content_includes_title":false,"authors":[{"nameParsed":{"literal":"Andrew Hutchings","given":"Andrew","family":"Hutchings"},"name":"Andrew Hutchings","id":"contributors-myst-generated-uid-0"}],"github":"https://github.com/LinuxJedi/Copperline","keywords":["amiga","emulator","ocs","ecs","rust"],"source_url":"https://github.com/LinuxJedi/Copperline/blob/main/docs/index.md","edit_url":"https://github.com/LinuxJedi/Copperline/edit/main/docs/index.md","thumbnail":"/docs/build/state-of-the-art-4c6a57cba1ceb9451e42007028a715d4.png","exports":[{"format":"md","filename":"index.md","url":"/docs/build/index-ddff25006b81600601f81231af7b2fc9.md"}]},"mdast":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"block","children":[{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":14,"column":1},"end":{"line":22,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Copperline is a cycle-driven Commodore Amiga emulator (OCS, ECS, and AGA)\nwritten in Rust. Cycle-driven means the whole machine -- the 68000-family\nCPU, Agnus, Denise, Paula, the CIAs, the floppy subsystem, and the chip bus\nthat ties them together -- advances on one colour-clock timeline: the chip\nbus is arbitrated per colour clock, the Copper and blitter are scheduled\nper DMA slot with the hardware bus sequences, and the Paula IPL pipe plus\n68000 interrupt sampling are modelled. That timing model is what lets\nit run the current cycle-sensitive OCS and AGA regression set, as well as\nKickstart, Workbench, games, and CDTV/CD32 titles.","position":{"start":{"line":14,"column":1},"end":{"line":14,"column":1}},"key":"BLdRGfeZdF"}],"key":"vrfqLlm63W"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":24,"column":1},"end":{"line":25,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The project home is ","position":{"start":{"line":24,"column":1},"end":{"line":24,"column":1}},"key":"uhXYhKAWG8"},{"type":"link","url":"https://copperline.dev/","position":{"start":{"line":24,"column":1},"end":{"line":24,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"copperline.dev","position":{"start":{"line":24,"column":1},"end":{"line":24,"column":1}},"key":"a3Dylu4r9z"}],"urlSource":"https://copperline.dev/","key":"WmOBV3h7xZ"},{"type":"text","value":"; the source\nlives on ","position":{"start":{"line":24,"column":1},"end":{"line":24,"column":1}},"key":"M8K4MIqNDp"},{"type":"link","url":"https://github.com/LinuxJedi/Copperline","position":{"start":{"line":24,"column":1},"end":{"line":24,"column":1}}